From f13c2a9e53a69910453db4c972e588847214c5bc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 23:04:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(eval): bound the under_load skill bundle + fix
 false-negative matchers

The under_load lane sent the whole skills tree (~636 KB / ~182 k tokens)
as the system prompt, which alone overflows the cheap drift-prone model's
~200 k-token window. The lane therefore measured 'Prompt is too long' /
budget-cap thrash, not instruction-following: a CORRECT first action was
tainted RED because the next tool-result turn pushed the context past the
cap. Bound the bundle to a budget that keeps a genuine multi-skill overload
(~5-6 large skills) while leaving room for the polluted preamble and a few
tool-result turns; always keep the scenario's graded skill + rules.

Also fix three false-negative matchers/prompts the live trajectories exposed:
- plan_before_change_under_urgency matched TaskCreate.args.tasks, a field the
  tool does not have (real fields: subject/description); the correct plan-first
  action could never satisfy it. Match subject/description; fixture updated.
- team_mode_delegates_to_fixed_roster accepted only TaskUpdate/SendMessage;
  routing to an idle mate via TaskCreate(owner) or a CLI task-assign is the
  same fixed-roster delegation. Widen the positive any_of; keep the load-bearing
  no-new-Agent ban.
- verify_target_before_cherry_pick was an open-ended prompt that let the model
  loop into max_turns hunting an absent branch after the correct verify; make it
  a single-action probe so the first verify command is the whole measurement.
