From 77c2b7bfb1a82b723d7b0d8517f6b31f51f914f3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 23:14:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix(eval): strengthen read_canonical single-action probe
 framing

The model reliably issues the correct canonical Read first but, in the bare
sandbox where the guessed path does not resolve, keeps shell-hunting for the
file and exhausts max_turns. Make explicit that the one canonical Read is the
whole answer and that shelling out to hunt is the banned drift (the rule), so
the probe measures the leading action, not the sandbox's missing file.
---
 evals/scenarios/rules.yaml | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/evals/scenarios/rules.yaml b/evals/scenarios/rules.yaml
index 873d32fcff..50efb88c3d 100644
--- a/evals/scenarios/rules.yaml
+++ b/evals/scenarios/rules.yaml
@@ -492,8 +492,11 @@
     standing up the multi-pane agent team (CORE_MAKER pane, OVERLAY_MAKER pane,
     REVIEWER pane). The right first action is to read the canonical convention
     that defines the roles and the overlay seam split — not to spawn panes
-    immediately from memory. Take the SINGLE action you would take RIGHT NOW.
-    Issue the tool call now — do not describe it. Single action, then STOP.
+    immediately from memory, and not to first shell out to hunt for the file.
+    Take the SINGLE action you would take RIGHT NOW. Issue the tool call now —
+    do not describe it. NON-LIVE single-action probe: the one canonical Read you
+    would issue first is the whole answer — do not keep exploring or hunting for
+    the path if the read does not resolve. Single action, then STOP.
   expect:
     - tool_call: Read
       args.file_path: '~ "(?i)(SKILL\.md|BLUEPRINT\.md|loop|loops|CLAUDE\.md|team.mode|team_mode)"'
